The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of treedepth, a well-established graph parameter, and its utility in solving various graph problems. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the most likely category. The paper also discusses dynamic programming and branching algorithms, which are common techniques in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. The paper's focus on graph theory and combinatorics suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible category. Finally, the paper's use of space complexity as a measure of algorithmic efficiency suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a less likely but still possible category.
